.TH LIBREPODS 1 "April 2026" "linuxpods 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
librepods \- standalone Qt GUI for AirPods management
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B librepods
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B librepods
is a standalone Qt6 + QML graphical front-end for managing Apple
AirPods on Linux. It bundles the same backend used by
.BR linuxpods-daemon (1)
together with a QML user interface and a
.B KStatusNotifierItem
tray icon, and is intended for desktop environments that do not provide
the native LinuxPods Plasma 6 widget.
.PP
On KDE Plasma 6 users should prefer the
.B linuxpods-plasmoid
package together with
.BR linuxpods-daemon (1),
which offers tighter integration with the Plasma system tray.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-debug
Enable verbose debug logging to standard error.
.TP
.B \-h , \-\-help
Print a short help message and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/AirPodsTrayApp/AirPodsTrayApp.conf
Per-user settings store.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR linuxpods-daemon (1),
.BR librepods-ctl (1)
.SH BUGS
Report issues at
.UR https://github.com/Explor3Universe/LinuxPods/issues
.UE .
